	affiliations = {National Institute of Telecom. (Inatel), Brazil; Fraunhofer Institute for Optronics, System Technologies and Image Exploitation IOSB, Karlsruhe, Baden-Wurttemberg, Germany; Next-Generation Mobile (XGMobile) Inatel, Brazil; Institute Industrial It (InIT) TH-OWL, Germany; Tshwane University of Technology, Department of Electrical Engineering, Pretoria, Gauteng, South Africa; The Council for Scientific and Industrial Research, EDT4IR Research Centre, Pretoria, Gauteng, South Africa},
	abstract = {With the increasing adoption of 5G networks in smart cities and Industry 4.0 applications, energy efficiency (EE) has become a critical concern, particularly for industrial Internet of Things (IIoT) devices that operate continuously in latency-sensitive environments. This paper presents a novel Paging Signal-Aware Ordered Statistical Decoding (PS-Aware OSD) algorithm to optimize energy use during paging operations. By intelligently predicting paging occasions (PO) based on historical patterns, the algorithm reduces unnecessary wake-ups in extended discontinuous reception (eDRX) cycles. Simulations demonstrate that this approach improves energy efficiency by up to 40%, reduces block error rate (BLER), and improves throughput and latency compared to standard third-generation partnership project (3GPP) paging techniques. The paper discusses practical implementation aspects, acknowledges system limitations, and proposes future work, including the integration of machine learning for dynamic paging optimization and the development of security measures against spoofing or unnecessary battery drain. © 2025 IEEE.},
